{"title":"Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #23: Cannondale SuperSix Evo","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-cannondale-supersix-evo","date":1743082878000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-cannondale-supersix-evo\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #23: Cannondale SuperSix Evo</a></p>\n\n<p>Whether you’re on the market for a new bike or just want to try out some of the world’s best, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days</a> offer a unique experience to test the latest top-end bikes from the leading brands on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next up in our rundown of some of the incredible bikes that you can test ride at this years Track Days is the Cannondale SuperSix Evo.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SuperSix is Cannondale’s all-round road race bike, ridden by the EF pro teams. <em>Cyclist</em> tech editor Sam Challis reviewed the bike at the end of 2023 and praised its handling, speed and comfort. The Hi-Mod 1 build he reviewed was built with the old SRAM Red AXS groupset and HollowGram wheels, and weighed in at 7.2kg for a size 56.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Read Sam’s full review <a href=\"http://Read Sam's full review here.\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cannondale SuperSix Evo will be at the following Track Days events:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>26<sup>th</sup> April 2025, Odd Down Cycle Track Bath,<br />17<sup>th</sup> May 2025, Lee Valley VeloPark London,<br />7<sup>th</sup> June 2025, The Brownlee Centre, Leeds</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information on Cyclist Track Days click <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n              